title: Crimson Classic XC: Osprey Men 5th, Women 9th to Wrap Up Regular Season
text: Men's 8k Results (pdf) TUSCALOOSA, Ala. -- Racing on the course that will host the NCAA South Regional in a month, the North Florida Cross Country teams both claimed Top 10 finishes at the Crimson Classic held at the Harry Pritchett Running Park. The UNF men finished fifth, while the women's team claimed a ninth-place showing."I'm very proud of our performance today with well over half our team running the fastest times of their careers," said head coach Jeff Pigg . "We had several runners best their career marks by over two minutes. We saw dramatic time improvements over last year's times on the same course, so we are definitely getting better as a team.
